        q: `A 31-year-old, sexually active, healthy woman has a 1-week history of a mucopurulent vaginal discharge. On pelvic examination, the cervix appears erythematous around the os, but no erosions or mass lesions are present. A Pap test shows numerous neutrophils, but no dysplastic cells. Which of the following infectious agents is most likely to produce these findings?`,
