        optionFeedback: [`Avoidance of tobacco products will not decrease the chances of HPV infection.`,`Consumption of a diet rich in vegetables will not decrease the chances of HPV infection.`,`Maintenance of an ideal body weight will not decrease the chances of HPV infection.`,`Use of oral contraceptives will not decrease the chances of HPV infection.`,`The lesion shown is high-grade squamous intraepithelial lesion (HSIL), a precursor of cervical cancer caused by high-risk HPV infection. Except for sexual abstinence, vaccination for human papillomavirus is the only way of preventing HPV infection. Despite its efficacy (nearly complete protection against high-risk oncogenic HPV types 16 and 18 which account for approximately 70% of cervical cancers), the vaccine does not protect against all high-risk HPV types and current guidelines recommend that cervical cancer screening be continued as in the past.`],
