        q: `A 34-year-old woman who has been using oral contraceptives for 10 years has a routine Pap test for the first time. The results indicate that dysplastic cells are present, consistent with a high-grade squamous intraepithelial lesion (HSIL). Surgical excision confirms HSIL.    Which of the following is the most likely molecular pathogenesis for this finding?`,
